reviews.text:
Upon arrival on covered terrace it took a very long time for the service to arrive, the couple who then arrived after us were helped first.
Decided to grab a bite to eat here (wrong decision).
My wife ordered a “wadden burger” with jalapenos peppers that we thought had disappeared by ferry to Terschelling. The sandwich I think came from the local supermarket and the bottom floated in the fat. There was also a kind of “cold” tomato salsa under the hamburger which made it very sticky, cold and soaky. The whole thing decorated with short-fried breakfast bacon, bah!
I ordered myself a schnitzel with mushrooms, onion and bacon.
The mushroom slices (about 3) as well as the red onion were far from being found.
I don't know what the schnitzel was fried in, but was brown on top and pale on the bottom, seemed to float in a kind of olive oil where the origin cannot be traced.... Very dirty! 
Also this decorated with breakfast bacon that has just "walked" through the pan, looked pale, bah!
The salad consisted of a few leaves of 2 colors of lettuce without any addition of a dressing oid.
No reason for us to eat here again.
Price / quality is far to be found, too much pays for this food!
The local snack bar serves better dishes in our opinion.

Had dinner here last night. That was the same last time. Waddenburger comes on a small white soft ball, hamburger was fried in a lot of fat so the bottom half of the ball was soaked. Not many fresh ingredients. Fat slices of tomato. Schnitzel was very pale at the bottom. Breakfast bacon was badly fried and the mushrooms had probably already left for Terschelling with the. For dining, this eatery is not recommended. For a cup of coffee / tea with cake it is fine. Everything is on the expensive side. Quality/price ratio is not okay when it comes to dining.

reviews.title: Lunch menu is limited
reviews.text: Limited card. Not much choice for vegetarians. Food fine. Beautiful terrace with a view of the Wadden Sea and the harbor.

reviews.title: They better try their best
reviews.text:
The thick fries in the brochure are a disappointment, this is the 2nd time that I have received pieces of waste for my plate. This gives the fries baker a big 4.

That's not how you treat customers...

reviews.title: Fine for a quick bite before the ferry
reviews.text: I wouldn’t seek this place out unless you’re catching the ferry, but it was a reasonable enough choice for having some lunch with 45 minutes to kill. The shrimp croquettes were tasty enough though to be honest they could have been chicken or beef. Service was prompt.

reviews.title: Sat on deck and watched the action.
reviews.text: Great location.  Service was excellent.  Everybody spoke English and all very helpful.  We only has coffee, hot chocolate and some apple tart, but it hit the spot!  Glass sides kept out very strong wind.

reviews.title: perhaps 'grand cafe' is overstating it, it is an average nice place for a bite or a drink
reviews.text: Perhaps 'grand cafe' is overstating it, it is a pretty average place to eat or have a drink. Nothing fancy. Prices are pretty average too. You can have coffee/tea and cake, do simple breakfast, lunch or dinner. The opening times are wide enough for you to enjoy a meal before or after stepping aboard the ferry.

reviews.title: Ripoff terrace for the lazy and unknown.
reviews.text: we went to this restaurant of the Doeksen shopping firm to have a drink. The Doeksen firm is the long owner of the ferry ships to the islands where they make hugh profits transporting tourists to and from the islands. On top of this the firm wanted a restaurant. The menu is basic basic, as the average ferry passenger is only interresed in the well known snacks and drinks. The staff is probably the same staff as in the ferries. The casual uninteressed stubborend staff members that served the ferrries. All in all not recommendable.

reviews.title: Nice view and cosy interior
reviews.text: Fine cafe when you're waiting for the ferry to go to Vlieland or Terschelling. The prices are average so not an expensive place for tourists. They have a menu for 10euros and several dishes like sandwiches, salads, pizza, meat and of course fish menus
